<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="896" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d896">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Señor Ojeda to Mr. Adee.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">New
                                    York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-24"><hi rend="italic">September 24,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I beg you to convey to His Excellency my deep sorrow for the untoward
                            accident, and my earnest wishes for his prompt and complete
                            recovery.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ojeda.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>